.TH "format_value_ccm" 9 "format_value_ccm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
format_value_ccm \- Format a value into a buffer, using a specified number of bytes (i.e. maybe writing value X into a 4 byte buffer, or maybe into a 12 byte buffer), as per the SPU CCM spec.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" format_value_ccm
.BI "(unsigned int val "  ","
.BI "u8 *buf "  ","
.BI "u8 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "val" 12
value to write (up to max of unsigned int)
.IP "buf" 12
(pointer to) buffer to write the value
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to use (0 to 255)
